{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-post-template-tsx","path":"/posts/a-tiny-syntactic-sugar-for-wrapping-a-scala-class-with-serializable-trait/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"a992f843-61a4-594d-9732-2f389d5f6304","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/4b190/sweet-alice.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/8ac56/sweet-alice.webp 240w,\n/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/d3be9/sweet-alice.webp 480w,\n/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/d00b9/sweet-alice.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/09b79/sweet-alice.jpg 240w,\n/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/7cc5e/sweet-alice.jpg 480w,\n/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/4b190/sweet-alice.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/4b190/sweet-alice.jpg\"\n            alt=\"sweet alice\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In Scala / Spark programming, we sometimes need to implement the <code class=\"language-text\">Serializable</code> trait for a class, for passing the data between the Spark executors. To achieve this, we could declare a companion object with an <code class=\"language-text\">apply</code> method, and then use the <code class=\"language-text\">apply</code> method to create an instance of the class. Here’s a tiny syntactic sugar for this.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"scala\"><pre class=\"language-scala\"><code class=\"language-scala\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token namespace\">scala<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>reflect<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span></span>ClassTag\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> SerializeVariable<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>T<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> ClassTag<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>constructor<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">=></span> T<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">AnyRef</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">with</span> Serializable <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token annotation punctuation\">@transient</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">private</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">lazy</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">val</span> instance<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> T <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> constructor\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> get<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> T <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> instance\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">object</span> SerializeVariable <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> apply<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>T<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> ClassTag<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>constructor<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">=></span> T<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> SerializeVariable<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>T<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> SerializeVariable<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>T<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>constructor<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The usage is simple, just wrap the class with the <code class=\"language-text\">SerializeVariable</code> class, and then use the <code class=\"language-text\">get</code> method to get the instance.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"scala\"><pre class=\"language-scala\"><code class=\"language-scala\"><span class=\"token comment\">// wrapper</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">val</span> normalizer <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> SerializeVariable<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> JsonRegexAspectNormalizer<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// extract</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> extract<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>normalizer<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> SerializeVariable<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>JsonRegexAspectNormalizer<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> JsonRegexAspectNormalizer <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> normalizer<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>get</code></pre></div>\n<p>That’s all. It’s a simple solution and easy to use. I hope you like it.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2019-07-03---A-Tiny-Syntactic-Sugar-for-Wrapping-a-Scala-Class-with-Serializable-Trait//posts/a-tiny-syntactic-sugar-for-wrapping-a-scala-class-with-serializable-trait","tagSlugs":["/tag/programming/","/tag/scala/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-07-03T20:00:00.000Z","description":"sometimes we need to implement the Serializable trait for a class, here's a tiny syntactic sugar.","tags":["Programming","Scala"],"title":"A Tiny Syntactic Sugar for Wrapping a Scala Class with Serializable Trait","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/6866f0a91149b0f6b36efb2383a06617/sweet-alice.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2019-07-03---A-Tiny-Syntactic-Sugar-for-Wrapping-a-Scala-Class-with-Serializable-Trait//posts/a-tiny-syntactic-sugar-for-wrapping-a-scala-class-with-serializable-trait"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","288581551","401334301"],"slicesMap":{}}